    "body": "Hey, sorry for the late reply.\r\n\r\nHardhat network always uses the chain id from your config, which defaults to 31337.\r\n\r\nWe decided to do this, including when forking a network, as signing txs with another network's id is a security risk. For example, a malicious test could steal your funds.\r\n\r\nIf you really need to use the remote network's id, you should set it in your config.",
