    "body": "@alcuadrado setting it in the `hardhat.config.ts` works flawlessly. However, I would like to start a fork local node using the `hardhat node --fork` cli flag. It will pick up the chainId from the config, but I would rather pass in the also the `chainId` dynamically on the cli, with an argument like `--chain-id`.\r\n\r\nCan we get a feature like that?\r\n\r\nExample usage:\r\n```\r\n> hardhat node --no-deploy --port 8545 --chain-id 56 --fork bscRPCUrl.com\r\n> hardhat node --no-deploy --port 8546 --chain-id 137 --fork polygonRPCUrl.com\r\n```\r\n\r\nA hacky workaround I use for now is:\r\n\r\n`hardhat.config.ts`\r\n```typescript\r\n{\r\nhardhat: {\r\n      chainId: process.env.FORK_CHAIN_ID ? Number(process.env.FORK_CHAIN_ID) : 1337\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\n> FORK_CHAIN_ID=137 hardhat node --no-deploy --port 8546 --fork polygonRPCUrl.com\r\n```",
